{
  "text": "As detailed below, we focus our attention on the adversary entity that decides which unreliable links to include in the network topology in each round of an execution in the dual graph model. We introduce a new type of adversary with constraints that better generalize the dynamic behavior of real radio links. We then reexamine simple back-off strategies originally introduced in the standard radio network model [CITATION_1] (which has only reliable links), and prove that for reasonable parameters, these simple strategies now do guarantee efficient communication in the dual graph model combined with our new, more realistic adversary.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "10965994"
